Abdomen notably longer than usual, 4.8 times longer than thoracic length; shiny, dark-brown, with sparse brown pruinescence on Tg1, Tg8 and sternites; bristles brown, short, sparse, longer on Tg1 and Tg2; St8 with some elongate yellow bristles on distal margin. Terminalia (
Figs. 52–55
): long and slender; right epandrial lamella twice longer than left lamella; right hypandrial lobe long, triangular, with short thin bristles, left hypandrial lobe not developed; dorsal bridge complete; postgonites slender, ribbon-like.
